stanford center at peking university the stanford challenge stanford center at peking university stanford center at peking university stanford is expanding its presence in one of the world's fastest growing nations the stanford center at peking university slated to open in beijing in 2012 will serve as a headquarters for stanford students and faculty conducting research in china in every field of study from political science to engineering scholars from both countries will combine their expertise on challenges like rural health care and education sustainable development and global economic stability housed in the new lee jung sen building the center will also house the bing overseas studies program in beijing comments are closed
